shared_text:
Cobden Jr-Sr High
August 27 at 8:08 AM ·

Update-

ALL baseball and softball games will be played at home today.

Jr High Softball 4:30
Jr High Baseball 4:30
High School Baseball to follow at 7:00

Anyone planning to attend baseball or softball games will need to bring their own chair. We encourage all fans to maintain social distance, we want to remind you to stay home if they feel sick or have any of the symptoms of COVID-19. When present at the game fans are expected to wear a mask at all times. There will be no concessions at this time. During baseball games home fans will be asked to sit behind the right field and center field fence. The visiting teams fans will be asked to sit along the left field line. The grand stand behind home plate will be used as extended dugouts for the players and will be off limits to all fans. During softball games home fans will be asked to sit along the first base side of the field or outfield. Visiting teams fans will be asked to sit along the third base side of the field. The bleachers behind home plate will be used as extended dugouts for the players and will be off limits to all fans.

Cobden Jr-Sr High
July 18 at 9:59 AM ·

GRADUATION ANNOUNCEMENT!

Graduation will take place outside on the baseball field at 7pm. Reserved seating is currently being revised and those assignments will be announced by 1:00 today. Parents and guests will be allowed to place chairs on the field beginning at 2:00. A public seating area will also be available for those wishing to attend. All guests should bring lawn chairs. Tents, umbrellas, banners, balloons, or other large items that may block the view of others will not be allowed. All guests must wear a mask until seated.

Seniors- please arrive no later than 6:30 so that you have time to listen to the revised processional plan considering this will be slightly different than we practiced.

All guests and graduates are encouraged to dress casually. It will be warm outside and the outfield area may still be wet in areas. Please plan accordingly.

Please call, email, or text Ms Mindy or Mr Shoemate with any questions.

*In the event of rain, each family has been assigned a classroom to watch the ceremony online. Parents only will be allowed in the gym for the ceremony.

shared_text:
Cobden Jr-Sr High
July 14 at 9:26 AM ·

We are super excited to honor the Class of 2020 this Saturday at 7pm.

Graduation practice will be held on Friday at 6pm. All Seniors will meet in the gym, please wear your mask into the building.

Family reserved seating has been assigned. Each guest must bring their own chair. Each rectangle should hold 10 chairs.

Parking will be available in the student parking lot and back around the new gym (Peach Festival Parking Area). Posted Handicapped parking will be available between the baseball field and the elementary building.

Additional Public seating space will be provided in the parking lot in front of the high school and in left field.

Graduates will be provided a chair.

Please do not bring tents, umbrellas, balloons, or banners. Large objects block the view of other guests.

Parents of graduates may approach the stage to take pictures of their graduate as the receive their diploma.

Masks must be worn until you are seated.

Good afternoon everyone. Here is the information for jr/sr high school students for the remainder of the school year:

Seniors have received their final packet.

We will have two more packet mailings: April 29th and May 13th.

There will be no "Finals" for any classes (except for dual credit).

Award day has been cancelled.

Jr/Sr High Students will have next week to clean out lockers. 8am-8pm M-F. We will monitor the hallways to make sure social distancing occurs.

Senior check out/Chromebook return will be on May 8th. 8am-4pm

HS and Jr. High Students will return Chromebooks May 26th-May 29th from 8am-8PM M-F.

Graduation has been moved to July 18th and Prom will take place on July 11th if social distancing restrictions have been lifted.

post_text:
Congratulations to Mr. Kenny Smith, a member of the 1964 Amazing Appleknockers basketball team, on being inducted into the Cobden High School Athletics Hall of Fame last night.
As quoted by Teri Campbell: Kenny was a senior and key member of Cobden’s state runner-up team in 1964, helping the Appleknockers compile a record of 32-3 that season. He was named to the All-Tournament team at the IHSA state tournament and earned all-conference honors as a junior and senior.

shared_text:
Carly O'Keefe KFVS is feeling inspired at Cobden Jr High School.
January 24 at 3:22 PM · Cobden, IL ·

Anyone need a good news pick-me-up this cold & dreary Friday? The two boys in the center of this picture have been through a whole lot. The tall boy (center left) is Kohen Moore of Cobden, Illinois. Kohen suffered life-threatening injuries in a bad car crash off Lick Creek Road & I-57 in Union County right before school started in August 2018. It was touch and go for a while. Doctors weren't sure he would pull through, but thanks to top-notch medical care, support from his best buddy Jackson Rendleman (center right), and countless (unceasing) prayers from the community -- Kohen lived up to his now locally famous hashtag #KohenStrong. Kohen is now back on the court playing basketball with his best friend Jackson -- who you may remember was our KFVS-TV Everyday Hero this time last year. If you missed the story, check it out here!!! ---> https://bit.ly/2RJ73hs. It's a great reminder of what true friendship is. ❤️
